- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses tree-to-tree transformations and their decomposition using combinators. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with transformations on trees, which are often used in formal language theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses functions and their composition, which are fundamental concepts in programming languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as tree-to-tree transformations are used in various AI applications such as natural language processing and image recognition.
